🔹 Models Overview
1. Pruned Feature Model (xgboost_model.ipynb)

This model uses a reduced set of 14 features that were originally selected from a linear regression baseline using VIF (Variance Inflation Factor) pruning.

Focus: simplicity and consistency with baseline models
Encoding: ordinal encoding for categorical variables
No class weighting
Designed to match the feature set used in logistic regression

👉 This model is easier to interpret but may lose useful information due to feature removal.

2. Expanded Feature Model (xgboost_model_2.ipynb

This model uses a larger set of features and removes only variables that could cause data leakage, such as burnout-related scores and mental health indicators (stress, depression, anxiety).

Focus: maximize predictive performance
Encoding:
ordinal encoding for ordered variables
one-hot encoding for nominal variables
Includes class imbalance handling using sample weights
Additional improvements tested:
Grid search tuning for hyperparameter optimization
Fixed regularized XGBoost to reduce overfitting

👉 This model allows XGBoost to capture more complex patterns in the data.
